// Page VillainOrRogue Text :
"P9320693" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Exotic Armor Schematics</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color orange><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You come across a series of blueprints that look similar to the armor the Rikti wore during their invasion. <br><br><scale 1.1><font face=computer><color BurlyWood>What's important about these blueprints is that there are annotations all along the margins:<br><br>'Shorten length of arms' 'Add shield emitter' 'Increase power output' 'Add anti-missile chaff'' 'More plutonium'.<br><br>The only problem with these blueprints is that they're not complete.  Some integral schematics are missing in order to fully assemble this military-grade armor.  On the back of one of the blueprints is a hastily scrawled message from the engineer who created these blueprints.  They state that he and the full blueprints were taken by the Rikti.  Printed on each blueprint is the location of the Arachnos lab where the blueprints were made.</scale></color></font><br><br>This armor belongs in your hands, not in the hands of whatever mad genius is assembling it.  You could track down where the Rikti took the Engineer and more importantly the blueprints.<br><br>Alternately, you could try raiding the Arachnos lab where the Engineer was working on the blueprints and likely prototype armor."
// Answer Text :
"P2625149635" "VILLAIN: Get the Rikti Armor blueprints."
// Answer Text :
"P2105949297" "ROGUE: Raid the Arachnos lab."
// Page Vigilante Text :
"P558980648" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Exotic Armor Schematics</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color orange><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You come across a series of blueprints that look similar to the armor the Rikti wore during their invasion.<br><br><scale 1.1><font face=computer><color BurlyWood>What's important about these blueprints is that there are annotations all along the margins: <br><br>'Shorten length of arms' 'Add shield emitter' 'Increase power output' 'Add anti-missile chaff' 'More plutonium'.<br><br>The only problem with these blueprints is that they're not complete.  Some integral schematics are missing in order to fully assemble this military-grade armor.  On the back of one of the blueprints is a hastily scrawled message from the engineer who created these blueprints.  They state that he and the full blueprints were taken by the Rikti.  Printed on each blueprint is the location of the Arachnos lab where the blueprints were made.</scale></color></font><br><br>Arachnos can't be allowed to create this armor.  Besides, you can likely make much better use of it than they ever could."
// Page UnableToInvestigate Text :
// Answer Text :
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 


