// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - DialogTree 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page VillainOrRogue Text :
"P511534885" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Extremely Annoying Ring Tone</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color orange><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You hear an extremely annoying ring tone in the distance that doesn't seem to be dying down. You ignore it for a few moments before finally moving to shut it off. The source of the ring tone seems to be a bright red PDA. You push a button on it to make the ringing stop, but something on the screen catches your eye - a link to a file called, 'Doc Quantum's Moral Questions'. You click on it...<br><br><scale 1.1><font face=computer><color BurlyWood>You're brought to a webpage full of large blocks of text. Reading it over, it belongs to the villain Doc Quantum, who is writing up various questions regarding morality.<br><br>His latest write up is in regards to the value of human life. Doc Quantum describes that he has stolen an important piece of Portal Corp technology and has agreed to bring it back in exchange for the hero, Miss Thystle. He muses that this will see just how far Portal Corp is willing to go for their research - will they give up the life of this heroine just for technology?<br><br></scale></color></font>You could look in to what lab Doc Quantum stole the technology from. It's probably still recovering...which means you could swoop in there and destroy the remains of it - after taking everything in there for yourself. You'll summon in some...alternate dimension 'issues' for the people to deal with. It will remind them of your presence and show the people of Paragon that 'philosophers' like Doc Quantum are small-time compared to you.<br><br>On the other hand, Doc Quantum's days as a hero are officially over - not that any one hasn't suspected that for some time. The time of this posting was very recent - enough that you surmise that Doc Quantum probably isn't done preparing for the delivery of Miss Thystle. To make a large amount of cash you could find out where Doc Quantum is, take him down, then change his deal to match whatever you want."
// Answer Text :
"P133004341" "VILLAIN: Wreak some havoc at the Portal Corp lab!"
// Answer Text :
"P4076875920" "ROGUE: Trick Doc Quantum to get Portal Corp tech!"
// Page Vigilante Text :
"P2799580341" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Extremely Annoying Ring Tone</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color orange><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You hear an extremely annoying ring tone in the distance that doesn't seem to be dying down. You ignore it for a few moments before finally moving to shut it off. The source of the ring tone seems to be a bright red PDA. You push a button on it to make the ringing stop, but something on the screen catches your eye - a link to a file called, 'Doc Quantum's Moral Questions'. You click on it...<br><br><scale 1.1><font face=computer><color BurlyWood>You're brought to a webpage full of large blocks of text. Reading it over, it belongs to the villain Doc Quantum, who is writing up various questions regarding morality.<br><br>His latest write up is in regards to the value of human life. Doc Quantum describes that he has stolen an important piece of Portal Corp technology and has agreed to bring it back in exchange for the hero, Miss Thystle. He muses that this will see just how far Portal Corp is willing to go for their research - will they give up the life of this heroine just for technology?<br><br></scale></color></font>Doc Quantum's mind was always corrupted - you knew it from day one. Now he spends his time musing about the morality of the world, testing and observing it. But what does he do to <i>change</i> it? Absolutely nothing - the man is a waste of space.<br><br>You...however...are different. You intend to change the world to what it should be, to what it <i>has</i> to be. First up is Portal Corp. If a blowhard like Doc Quantum was able to steal from them, it means that the people there have become too...<i>complacent</i>. And if they just simply send this heroine out to get their technology back...what will they learn? Nothing. <br><br>Someone needs to show Portal Corp the harshness of the world - maybe then they will actually take their responsibility <i>seriously</i>."
// Answer Text :
"P1057256357" "VILLAIN: Teach Portal Corp a valuable lesson!"
// Page UnableToInvestigate Text :
// Answer Text :
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 


