// Page VillainOrRogue Text :
"P820007354" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Bloody Bane Spider Helmet</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color orange><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You nearly trip over a small object on the ground. Upon inspection, you see it is a helmet belonging to a bane spider, with blood splattering the outside and inside of it. Whoever was wearing this must have been in quite the battle, though it isn't normal for Bane Spiders to discard their gear like this. You investigate this further by utilizing the tech inside the helmet to gather information about whoever discarded this...<br><br><scale 1.1><font face=computer><color BurlyWood>It seems Arachnos has issued a bounty on a group of Bane Spiders - they've broken off from the mental network that comprises the soldiers and are trying to flee the Rogue Isles. This happened in the midst of an assault on a Longbow base in Grandville - now both Longbow and Arachnos are seeking these Bane Spiders, both offering a large reward for them.<br><br></scale></color></font>You've heard of this happening before to a Bane Spider here and there - that was the last time you heard of those specific operatives, however. Arachnos is swift to handle any issue with the Bane Spiders, though now it appears to have become widespread within this group.<br><br>You could investigate where one of these Bane Spiders has run off to and collect on that bounty - either from Arachnos or Longbow. It would be a fairly good payday from either group and earn you some influence with one of the two groups.<br><br>Then again...it sounds as if the squad was in the middle of attacking a Longbow base when they disbanded. That means there's a group of Longbow out there still operating - still tracking everyone's movements, including your own. That's something that...can't be allowed to remain. Not when they're teetering on the brink of destruction."
// Answer Text :
"P2371038981" "VILLAIN: Destroy the Longbow base!"
// Answer Text :
"P2939678148" "ROGUE: Collect the Bane Spider bounty!"
// Page Vigilante Text :
"P4060292112" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Bloody Bane Spider Helmet</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color orange><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You nearly trip over a small object on the ground. Upon inspection, you see it is a helmet belonging to a bane spider, with blood splattering the outside and inside of it. Whoever was wearing this must have been in quite the battle, though it isn't normal for Bane Spiders to discard their gear like this. You investigate this further by utilizing the tech inside the helmet to gather information about whoever discarded this...<br><br><scale 1.1><font face=computer><color BurlyWood>It seems Arachnos has issued a bounty on a group of Bane Spiders - they've broken off from the mental network that comprises the soldiers and are trying to flee the Rogue Isles. This happened in the midst of an assault on a Longbow base in Grandville - now both Longbow and Arachnos are seeking these Bane Spiders, both offering a large reward for them.<br><br></scale></color></font>The Bane Spider's mind link breaking must mean one thing - Arachnos is losing control and Longbow is trying to free these soldiers. Which is ridiculous - in the time it took to try to cripple the mental network of the Bane Spiders, Longbow could have wiped out a number of their squads and gained some ground. But now this new policy of theirs seems to be spreading - if it proves successful, who knows what it will mean next? <br><br> Instead of trying to stop Paragon Protectors in one day, will they spend two weeks to try to revert them? There's no time to do that - justice needs to be <i>swift</i> and <i>harsh</i>, not slow and merciful.<br><br>The Longbow base that was assaulted would be searching for the Bane Spiders now - they may even be harboring some of them. You need to go in there and <color red>put them down</color> for their own good."
// Answer Text :
"P1803356233" "VILLAIN: Attack the Longbow base!"
// Page UnableToInvestigate Text :
// Answer Text :
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 


