// Page VillainOrRogue Text :
"P352215572" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Just How Evil Are You?</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color orange><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You receive a communicator message from the twisted Doc Quantum.<br><br><scale 1.1><font face=computer><color BurlyWood>This depraved pseudo-scientist has issued one of his famous moral challenges.  The message reads:<br><br></scale></color></font><color orange>{HeroName},<br><br>I have prepared a fun little experiment that I know we will both enjoy.  One of my favorite subjects, Hollow Point, has subdued three of Paragon's most patriotic heroes with the aid of his ex-Council cronies.  I know these <i>Virtuous Champions of Justice</i> have probably caused you trouble in the past and I give them to you as a gift.  Their costumes have been removed, their powers suppressed.  All you have to do is get into the sewers that Hollow Point and his ex-Council cronies are hiding in and...well, it's up to you from there.  They're waiting for your judgment, {HeroName}!  Do with them what you will.<br><br>Oh, I almost forgot.  There's a catch.  You're not the only one I made this offer to.  Best of luck to you.</color><br><br>You could enter the sewers and pummel those heroes silly as well as stop anyone who gets in your way.<br><br>Alternatively you could give those heroes a break and free them; they will definitely owe you a favor for saving their heroic hides."
// Answer Text :
"P69129550" "VILLAIN: Eliminate weakened heroes."
// Answer Text :
"P1058444237" "ROGUE: Get those heroes out of there."
// Page Vigilante Text :
"P357575928" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Just How Evil Are You?</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color orange><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You receive a communicator message from the twisted Doc Quantum.<br><br><scale 1.1><font face=computer><color BurlyWood>This depraved pseudo-scientist has issued one of his famous moral challenges.  The message reads:<br><br></scale></color></font><color orange>{HeroName},<br><br>I have prepared a fun little experiment that I know we will both enjoy.  One of my favorite subjects, Hollow Point, has subdued three of Paragon's most patriotic heroes with the aid of his ex-Council cronies.  I know these <i>Virtuous Champions of Justice</i> have probably caused you trouble in the past and I give them to you as a gift.  Their costumes have been removed, their powers suppressed.  All you have to do is get into the sewers that Hollow Point and his ex-Council cronies are hiding in and...well, it's up to you from there.  They're waiting for your judgment, {HeroName}!  Do with them what you will.<br><br>Oh, I almost forgot.  There's a catch.  You're not the only one I made this offer to.  Best of luck to you.</color><br><br>If the heroes in question are who you think they are, they've worked with you in the past.  You can't have them spilling all of your secrets to whoever else might come along.  Sorry guys, it's nothing personal."
// Page UnableToInvestigate Text :
// Answer Text :
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 


